      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "**llama.cpp server feature parity** — four recent llama-server capabilities, wired into the grounded chat agent.\n\n- **Parallel tool calls** — read-only tools requested in one turn run concurrently; a batch containing a write tool stays sequential. A `search_vault` + `search_references` + `read_file` turn is now one round trip, not three.\n- **Perf + cache readout** — the per-answer footer reports generation speed and KV prompt-cache reuse — `… · 41 tok/s · 1.2k cached` — read from `timings.predicted_per_second` and `usage.prompt_tokens_details.cached_tokens`.\n- **Answer now** — a persistent button that ends an over-thinking model's reasoning mid-stream (`reasoning_control` → `POST /v1/chat/completions/control`), then stops tool-calling and forces the answer. No-ops gracefully where the endpoint is absent.\n- **Cold-start awareness** — reads the router's `/v1/models` `status.value`; a sleeping/loading model shows \"Waking the model (cold start…)\" instead of a blank wait, and the settings model picker shows each model's load state.\n\nStill read-only out of the box. Needs the [qmd](https://github.com/tobi/qmd) CLI plus a local OpenAI-compatible LLM (llama-server / LM Studio). Obsidian 1.7.2+.",
